The paper also involves the use of failure detectors, which is a common tool in the study of distributed systems and algorithms, and thus falls under the subfield of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof techniques, which are central to the subfield of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also deals with synchronization and agreement problems, which are central topics in the subfield of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new way of thinking about failure detectors, which can be seen as a contribution to the subfield of Programming Languages (cs.PL).
